The monotony of featureless grey and white walls is alleviated only by the occasional appearance of the Earth Alliance insignia. It's not much of an improvement. Years ago, control would have been the bustling heart of any ship. In the latest single-crew, single-AI vessels, it's an empty room that contains only an acceleration couch, a small info screen, and a documentation tablet, tethered to the couch so it doesn't get lost amid all the clutter.

