> examine document file

> examine document file
Ships' document files contain rudimentary information on those vanishingly few functions of a starship that its human crew members are allowed anywhere near. This information, accessible via a tablet display tethered to the acceleration couch in Command, is what you could describe as optimised for the hard of thinking.
Available documents: a computer manual, a comms manual, a weapons manual, a sanitation manual, a medbay manual and a radio manual.
> examine computer manual

> examine computer manual
ABOUT YOUR COMPUTER

The ship's computer is a fully functional artifical intelligence, managed by state-of-the-art Earth Alliance technologies.

To interact with the computer, please state computer, followed by your query.
For example: computer open pod bay doors, computer date, computer mission.

Note that system performance may be adversely affected by combat damage, meteorite strikes and explosure to high EM sources. Should this occur, rest assured that critical systems have heavy redundancy, cease attempts to communicate with the AI immediately and request return to the neares EA base at the soonest available opportunity.
> s

> s

You are in the Archive.

This brightly lit room is so small that you could touch each wall just by stretching out your arms. Its dazzling white walls are blank and unadorned, but for four drawers.

You can see a green drawer, a blue drawer, a white drawer and a black drawer.
You can go north.
> open green drawer

> open green drawer
You open it.
It contains a photograph.
> get photograph

> get photograph
You pick it up.
> examine photograph

> examine photograph
The old-fashioned printed photograph reminds you of days before the war.
It was taken at a protest march back on Luna. You, A. and the SmartDogs carrying red and black flags and placards protesting Earth Alliance expansionism. EA peacekeepers and conscription trucks are visible in the background.
There's a note written on the back.
> read photo

> read photo
On the back of the photograph, a note reads: Anti-war protests, Luna, 28831010.  Never forget who you are. Always. A.
> open blue drawer

> open blue drawer
You open it.
It contains a letter.
> get letter

> get letter
You pick it up.
> read letter

> read letter
Dear Z.,

It's funny, knowing we're both about to ship out at the same time and not being able to even see you before I go. I suppose they can't take the risk that the conditioning will fall away after all the hard work everyone's put into setting us straight, making us good officers. I'm getting my own command. I hear you are, too. I guess mutual congratulations are in order.

I still remember everything from before: the activism, the syndicate, the protests when the EA overruled the Luna council of representatiives. But it's like it all happened a long time ago, to someone else, who I'm kind of embarassed to think about ever having been. I guess that's what growing up must be like for everyone.

Anyway, I'll sign off now. I have to choose what I'm taking with me to [REDACTED]. I'll send you the next move in our game soon.

As always, A.

> open white drawer

> open white drawer
You open it.
It contains a gun.
> get gun

> get gun
You take the gun. You experience a momentary light scratching sensation as it samples your skin for genetic authentication. It feels heavy and somehow right in your hand.
> open black drawer

> open black drawer
You open it.
It contains a leaflet.
> read leaflet

> read leaflet
EARTH ALLIANCE!
 Our service personnel are the best because we MAKE them that way.

For millenia, the armed services have relied on mass conscription, in the process stripping the best and brightest out of the workforce and the gene pool. In Earth Alliance, we do things differently, ensuring not only that your hard-working children stay at home, but also successfully taking on society's most antisocial and desctructive youth and reforming them into the galaxy's finest fighting force!

Our state-of-the-art mental conditioning program turns a rag-tag bunch of anarchists and troublemakers into TRUE PATRIOTS, willing to fight and die to protect Earth, the Alliance, and our natural right to extend our reach among the stars.

 Meanwhile, if your neighbourhood anarchists are causing you trouble, just contact EA and we'll take them off your hands. Report antisocial behaviour to enlistment@earthalliance.ea.
