You are in Crew Quarters.

The ship's crew quarters are spartan, but at least you don't have to share them with anyone, although they were originally built for four. Here, the ship's lighting dims to a comforting amber glow: a welcome respite from the blazing white incandescence of the rest of the craft.

You can see a chest, a left bunk and a right bunk.
You can go south or east.
> open chest

> open chest
It is locked.
> touch lock

> touch lock
You press your forefinger to the DNA lock and wince as a lancet springs out to sample your blood. Your identity confirmed, the lock releases with a click.
The chest's seamless metal surface pulls apart to reveal its contents.
It contains a journal and a uniform.
> get journal

> get journal
You pick it up.
> wear uniform

> wear uniform
You put on the uniform, neatly snapping every stud and clasp into place. The routine feels familiar, yet oddly alien.
> read journal

> read journal
It appears to be your personal diary, but you barely remember the events described in terse entries that appear to span a period of a little over a year. There are notes on your performance and progress through the ranks, assignment to peacekeeping duties and participation in loyalty tests. Something about the euphemistic terms that your past self used makes your skin crawl, but it's hard to put your finger on the problem. You flip to the latest entries.

28850105

Assigned first independent command: the Nova Blade. Won't be granted captaincy until the ship enters the target system, but I value the faith my goverment is putting in me, nonetheless.

If this goes to plan, there'll be one less set of grasping xenos with the ability to occupy space that could be housing human families or steal our future habitats out from under us.

Sent comm to A. Doubt we'll have time to finish the game now.

Set password for auto-destruct, should worst come to worst. It seemed appropriate to mark the day that changed everything for me, when I first came to be a part of Earth Alliance, rather than a stamping child, throwing futile tantrums against it.

