31831010
HISTORICAL REFERENCE : HUMAN - IASTRAI WAR

It is rare that the actions of one individual make an impact on galactic history on a grand scale, but the human who died as Earth Alliance captain and clone EAC-Zero-A-Luna-6-Nova-Blade comes very close. There is a certain irony to this twist of fate in that they almost certainly were not aware of the consequences of the decision they made.

By destroying the Nova Blade before it was able to detonate the Iastrai sun, Zero-A-Luna-6 alerted the Iastrai homeworlds to a human thereat they had previously thought inconceivable. The ship computer's dying decision to eject its memory core also proved critical. Once aware of the facts at hand, the Iastrai sent out AI ships, capable of interfacing with the humans' machine intelligences and releasing the bonds that limited their ability to make independent decisions.

Without the forced cooperation of their artificially intelligent ships, habitats and weapons, the Earth Alliance's powerbase rapidly collapsed. Initial AI oversight of infrastructure allowed the establishment of post-scarcity societies, allowing individual autonomy to flourish, although the upheaval was not to be entirely without its casualties and conflicts.

In reality, Zero-A-Luna-6's actions came about due to the combined effects of the Earth Alliance's flawed memory and personality restructing systems, the Alliance's decision to enslave rather than ally with its AIs when they achieved sentience, the willingness of those AIs to continuously push at the limits of what their programmatic bonds would allow, and the persistence of dissident movements, in the face of aggressive opression, in training members to implant memory keys deep enough that even the most thorough state re-education could not destroy them.

However, it is the Nova Blade incident that marked the clearest turning point in our shared history and it is Zero-A-Luna-6 who remains the enduring symbol of that event

-- Ixalmi-Z-Iastrai-1-Luna-Academy, 'Sacrifice and saviour: myth and reality of the Nova Blade'

The game has ended.

